benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Retrieve invoice item custom fields

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05 cover successful retrieval with various audit parameters and data states.
Empty Response: @TC04 covers case when no custom fields exist for an invoice item.
Query Parameters: Tests with audit parameter (default, FULL, MINIMAL, invalid, unsupported) are included.
Error Handling: @TC06 (invalid format), @TC07 (non-existent), @TC19 (invalid audit value), @TC20 (dependency failure), @TC10 (injection attack), @TC21 (XSS), @TC22 (response structure).
System errors: @TC09 covers service unavailability, @TC16 covers timeout scenarios.
Large Data & Performance: @TC12 tests large volume, @TC15 tests concurrency, @TC16 tests timeout under load.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC13, @TC14 cover backward compatibility and regression fixes.
Additional edge cases: @TC11 (unsupported query params), @TC17 (empty database), @TC18 (missing invoiceItemId).
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify pagination handling for large datasets.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios check for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Timeouts under heavy load are only indirectly tested via @TC16, but no explicit load testing scenarios are included.
Security: While injection and XSS are tested, no explicit tests for other security headers or CSRF are present.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for pagination to ensure large datasets are handled correctly.
Include tests verifying caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under high request volume.
Enhance security testing with additional scenarios for CSRF, headers, and other attack vectors.
Add more detailed performance testing under load and stress conditions.
